The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry

                    The American Friends of The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry is a non-profit organisation with tax-exempt status under section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code. Employer Identification Number: 45-2062094.

The American Friends areas of interest are similar to those of The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry, a charity formed under the laws of England. The American Friends organisation frequently makes grants to The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry to support its programs or co-invests in charities selected by the American Friends organisation.

Through funds raised at the Foundation Polo Challenge in Santa Barbara, California, grants from the American Friends have supported the Foundation’s work with Walking With The Wounded, SSAFA mentoring project and the creation of the Endeavour Fund.

Contributions to the American Friends organisation by a US taxpayer are tax deductible for U.S. tax purposes to the full extent allowed by U. S. law. Please contact info@americanfriendsroyalfoundation.com for further information.                  





